<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In continue of issue ZF-3348</p>

<p>Zend_OpenId_Provider returns "openid.mode=cancel" in check_immediate mode (protocol version 1.1). But OpenID 1.1 specification says (par. 4.2.2.1.) that "openid.mode" must be <em>always</em> equal "id_res" in check_immediate mode, regardless of positive or negative response. For all awailable for me OpenID 1.1 consumers "cancel" response immediately breaks auth process.</p>

<p>See <a href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-authentication-1_1.html#mode_checkid_immediate">http://openid.net/specs/…</a> and <a href="http://openidenabled.com/resources/openid-test/checkup">http://openidenabled.com/resources/openid-test/…</a> for tests.</p>

